00:55:58,004 --> 00:56:25,595
made up of local residents, or they could have used the money to rebuild a garage that was behind Colleen's slash Salvatore's. The problem would have been solved. Instead, the city agreed to pay $1 million to Republic Parking for the installment of the meters. This corporation has nothing to invest in our community. The headquarter region is in Tennessee, a far cry from a local community. The city officials cannot say that this money

132
00:56:25,814 --> 00:56:42,723
that will gain from the meters will be reinvested in the community for the upkeep and of the roads and sidewalks currently. Why? Because one, we have a surplus budget now that can cover those costs. And two, Medford receives money for maintenance from the Massachusetts Office of Transportation because of Route 60, a state highway.

